# Node-1 Data Source Specification  
*(GDSC-based IC50 Measurement Layer)*

---

## 1. Primary Dataset

Node-1 measurements are derived from:

- Genomics of Drug Sensitivity in Cancer (GDSC)
  - GDSC1
  - GDSC2

---

## 2. Data Access Method

Raw dataset is **not stored in this repository**.

Data is accessed through:

> IC50 Explorer App (GitHub-hosted)

This app functions as the **Node-1 data access layer**, enabling:

- tumor-type filtering  
- mutation-based stratification  
- drug-level IC50 extraction  

---

## 3. Data Type

Primary measurement:

- IC50 (half-maximal inhibitory concentration)

Optional (if used):

- AUC

---

## 4. Query Context

Data is queried under the following conditions:

- Tumor types:
  - LUAD  
  - PDAC  
  - CRC  

- Mutation stratification:
  - KRAS-mut  
  - KRAS-WT  

---

## 5. Probe Definition

Drug probes are defined externally in:

> `probe_registry.md`

Each probe maps to a biological axis (e.g., MEK, EGFR).

---

## 6. Data Handling Policy

- No raw IC50 dataset is stored in this repository  
- All data is **query-based and dynamically retrieved**  
- All Node-1 outputs must be traceable to:
  - dataset (GDSC1 / GDSC2)  
  - query conditions  
  - probe selection  

---

## 7. Versioning Policy

- Dataset version (GDSC1 vs GDSC2) must be explicitly recorded in runs  
- Query conditions must remain fixed within a run  
- No mixing of dataset versions within a single execution  

---

## 8. Limitations

- Not all probes may be present in GDSC  
- Some axes may have limited or noisy signal  
- Absence of data must be recorded explicitly  
- Missing probes must not be inferred or substituted silently  

---

## 9. System Role

This specification defines:

> **where Node-1 data comes from and how it is accessed**

It does not define:

- interpretation  
- ranking logic  
- hypothesis generation  

These are handled in downstream nodes.
